# railwayc — credentials. railwayc's token is PROJECT-SCOPED, so its home is the
# CONSUMING PROJECT's .env(.local); paste these keys there. The cascade is two
# tiers: project .env(.local) > process env (no flag, no user-config tier).
# `railwayc help` is the full credential model.
# PUBLIC REPO: never commit real values. Leave blank here; fill only the copy.

# Railway PROJECT token — scoped to one project + one environment. Create it in
# Railway → your project → Settings → Tokens. Secret — never commit.
RAILWAY_TOKEN=

# Optional, NOT secret — the Railway project (name or id) this token is meant for.
# When set, `railwayc doctor` asserts the token points there and exits 7 on
# mismatch. Leave blank to skip the check.
RAILWAYC_EXPECT_PROJECT=
